      "content": "Combining clarithromycin with simvastatin can significantly increase the risk of serious muscle symptoms like rhabdomyolysis because clarithromycin interferes with how your body breaks down simvastatin. It is generally safer to space these medications at least 1 to 2 hours apart to minimize this interaction, though consulting your doctor or pharmacist for personal advice is always recommended. Please do not change your medication schedule without checking with your healthcare provider first.",
